The paper proposes a new architecture for modeling sequential data using stochastic latent variables and dilated convolutions. This falls under the category of machine learning and specifically, deep learning. The paper also mentions natural speech generation and human motion modeling, which are applications of this architecture. Therefore, the likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Sound), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
